!TITLE
IS YOUR BAIT WORKING?
!WORDS
 »Are we stuck always using the same bait?  Just because it worked in 
another time and place does not mean it will work everywhere.«
 The Lord Jesus commanded us to fish for men.  If we are to be 
successful in doing that, we must find out what kind of "bait" will 
be most effective in attracting men to the Gospel. A men's prayer 
group at a church in Ontario decided the best bait would be to meet 
the felt needs of the men in their community.  They identified four 
elements which they thought would attract men to an outreach event:  
friendship, a high quality presentation, good food, and sports.
   They began having a bimonthly dinner, using the same format as a 
businessmen's seminar.  In order to get Christian men together with 
non-Christian men in a non-threatening setting, they reserve a 
private room at a local restaurant.  In order to attend, each man 
from the church is required to bring a lost friend, neighbor, or 
co-worker. (Those who want to attend without bringing someone were 
reminded that the purpose of the meeting is outreach not 
fellowship.)  This guarantees that half the group will be men who 
need to hear the Gospel.
   After the meal, a master of ceremonies opens the meeting with 
several jokes to relax everyone and break the ice.  The main speaker 
is a Christian athlete, attorney, financial expert, or businessman 
who makes a presentation about his area of expertise and weaves in a 
personal testimony of how Christ has made a difference in his life.  
In the discussions and casual conversations afterwards the Christian 
men find many opportunities to interact about the claims of Christ on 
a personal level.  So far four men have become Christians.
      "If your bait working?" by Chuck Gianotti. Interest, Jan 1991. 
Pages 8-9.
!TOPICS
EVANGELISM, FRIENDSHIP
MEN, OUTREACH TO
FISHING FOR MEN
WITNESSING
OUTREACH TO MEN
MALE EVANGELISM
GIANOTTI, CHUCK
INTEREST, 9101 PP8-9
