!TITLE
FITNESS PROFILE EVALUATION
!WORDS
Before beginning an exercise program it is wise to get a risk factor 
evaluation from your physician, along with a medical examination.  
Then study the factors will which affect your progress.  These 
factors include body composition and evaluation(tested by the mirror 
test, full body photographs before and after, girth measurements, 
skin-fold measurements, and the bathroom scale); aerobic capacity 
(tested by the step-up test, treadmill test, bicycle ergometer); 
flexibility (tested by sit- and-reach); and muscle strength (tested 
by push-ups, abdominal curl, etc.).  Then a training program can be 
tailored to your needs and abilities.
     "Fitness profile evaluation" by Bill Gvoich. Vibrant Life, 
Mar/Apr 1987.  Pages 14-19.
!TOPICS
PHYSICAL FITNESS
EXERCISE
HEALTHFUL LIVING
GVOICH, BILL
VIBRANT LIFE, 8703- P14-19
