!TITLE
MARY CAN TEACH MEN A THING OR TWO
!WORDS
What can men learn from Mary, the Mother of Jesus? Humility, as 
mothers are grounded in the little things of life, honoring small 
tasks and service. Fertility, which makes mankind a bit like God, in 
the ability to "give birth with their hands and their imaginations."  
Patience.  Roots, not only awareness of spiritual ancestors, but the 
model of persons with faith and spiritual experience.  Mary knew who 
she was, how she related to God, and how she fit into the world.  
"She inspires me to examine both her tradition (Judaism) and my own 
(Catholicism) as sources of nourishment and vision--and not to 
abandon them for something more novel or trendy."  Vision, as modern 
Christians need personal vision to set them apart from the world and 
to direct and move their lives; and that visions can be trusted, and 
visions grow out of one's roots.  "Human beings need roots and 
wings." And, as Mary had to, man can learn to let go.

     "Mary can teach men a thing or two" by Kenneth Guentert.  U. S. 
Catholic, Oct 1988. Pages 36-37.
!TOPICS
CHRISTIAN LIVING
VISION
SERVICE
HUMILITY
VIRGIN MARY
MARY
G, KENNETH
UENTERT. U. S. CATHOLIC, 8810 PP36-37
