!TITLE
BAPTIST PASTOR WANTS TO RECLAIM DYING CHURCHES
!WORDS
John Bisagno, former pastor of First Baptist Church of Houston,  
declared his 11,000-member church is large enough and should start 
100 missions by the year 2000.  One main thrust will be reclaiming 
dying churches.  112 of the city's 246 Baptist churches have declined 
to less than 100 members. Missions will also include traditional 
suburban missions, language missions and apartment churches.
