!TITLE
THE DESPERATE NEED FOR BIBLICAL TRUTH IN OUR CHURCHES
!WORDS
"God made us for living.  We are designed to function at various 
levels: physical (the body), mental and emotional (the soul) and 
religious (the spirit)."  "If the body is crippled or diseased, 
living is impaired and made difficult.  If the soul is hampered, 
crushed or limited, living is seriously reduced.  If the spirit is 
deprived of ...faith, our capacity to live becomes primitive and 
animal-like."  As Jesus told Satan in the wilderness, the Word of God 
is the only thing that prevents chaos, devastation and 
meaninglessness.  Without it, our souls, mental powers, emotional 
balance, judgement and bodies show the effects.  Such is the 
experience of those who experience drugs, pornography, abortion, 
divorce, homosexuality, prejudice and racism, corruption, materialism 
and greed, and other life problems of our times.  The secret of true 
living is found in Scripture and is made visible by the exhibition of 
love, joy and peace.  Love is demonstrated by service and care; joy 
by a thankful spirit and hope and encouragement, and peace "...as the 
absence of panic and anxiety exhibiting patience and forgiveness."  
The truth of Scripture "...is grounded in the crucifixion, burial and 
resurrection of Jesus and in the presence of the Holy Spirit in the 
believer...."  This truth, leading to the practices and lifestyle 
which will manifest love, joy, and peace, must be the central theme 
from the pulpit.  "This is God's plan to change the world."
    "The desperate need for Biblical truth in our churches" by Ray C. 
Stedman.  Decision, Dec 1989.  Pages 23-24.
!TOPICS
BIBLE
CHRISTIAN LIFE
LOVE
JOY
PEACE
WORKS OF THE FLESH
SIN, RESULTS OF
FRUIT OF THE SPIRIT
