sometimes subconsciously, sometimes painfully.  Even when learned in 
childhood, it often falters in adolescence, when desire takes on new 
forms and an anarchic intensity, and then the young brain is awash 
with hormones and with the erotic imagery of popular culture.  The 
adult who tells an adolescent, 'You have the right to obey your 
impulses' is guilty of treachery to the adolescent as well as to the 
community."
