!TITLE
TEN SHORT YEARS
!WORDS
  "Suppose someone a short decade ago had predicted that within ten 
years the world would see the disappearance of the Soviet Union, the 
decommunization of Eastern Europe, the unification of Germany, the 
bloody breakup of Yugoslavia, the end of apartheid in South Africa, 
the marketization of China, near-revolutionary political upheavals in 
Japan and Italy, and now the handshake on the White House lawn 
between the prime minister of Israel and the head of the Palestine 
Liberation Organization....  The failure of predictions permits us to 
act as if our choices make a difference."
                         --Arthur Schlesinger, Jr.
                   (quoted in World, Sep 25, 1993)
