!TITLE
WOODSTOCK COMES TO WASHINGTON
!WORDS
  » "The next generation of young people should be prepared to enter 
an adult sexual life with a better base of attitudes and information 
than we have provided so far."   --Kristine Gebbie«

   Since the 1960s this country and the entire western world has been 
undergoing a "sexual revolution" that had broken down centuries-old 
moral codes.  We have become a sex-saturated society.  Children today 
are taught things in school that weren't even mentioned in polite 
society before.  Those who oppose this state of affairs are labeled 
as "extremists" by the media, which proves to what extent these 
revolutionary ideas have become the mainstream.  Yet Kristine Gebbie, 
President Clinton's new "AIDS czar" has set forth her agenda for 
reform by saying that the United States should stop being such a 
"repressed, Victorian society."

   Abortion, divorce, promiscuity, adultery, and sexually transmitted 
diseases have become epidemic, but Miss Gebbie maintains that our 
society "misrepresents information, denies sexuality early, denies 
homosexual sexuality-- particularly in teens--and leaves people 
abandoned with no place to go."
   This argument is not new.  At least since the 1920s, the elites in 
this country have been telling the common people that they have too 
many hang-ups and prejudices when it comes to sex. C. S. Lewis wrote 
in the early '40s:  "You and I, for the last 20 years, have been fed 
all day long on solid lies about sex. We have been told, till one is 
sick of hearing it, that sexual desire is in the same state as any of 
our other natural desires and that if only we abandon the silly 
Victorian idea of hushing it up, everything in the garden will be 
lovely....  They tell you sex has become messed up because it was 
hushed up.  But for the last 20 years it has not been hushed up. It 
has been chattered about all day long.  Yet [it] is still in a mess."

   Aggressive antipuritanism has become respectable.  Yet the most 
telling indictment against the revolution that Gebbie is championing 
is the destruction it has wreaked in the home.

      "Woodstock comes to Washington" by Gary Bauer.  First Things, 
Feb 1994 (No 40).  Pages 7- 9.  Topic: SEXUAL MORALITY. See also 9124 
and 8509.
!TOPICS
SEXUAL MORALITY
MORALS
LIBERATION, SEXUAL
