!TITLE
THE ULTIMATE TENDER WARRIOR
!WORDS
  » "We've looked in all the wrong places for our images of manhood.  
Jesus Christ is the ultimate man, the perfect role model."«

   Try to picture Jesus, and your mind automatically shifts to that 
famous, ever-present portrait showing Jesus as a long-haired, 
effeminate individual.  Hollywood persists in portraying Jesus as 
someone halfway between here and somewhere else, His mind never quite 
in touch with reality.  The real Jesus--and the real model for true 
manhood--is much more than those images.

   While words like caring, loving, firm, strong, kind, unselfish, 
and pure accurately describe Jesus, the overriding characteristic of 
His life was a sense of purpose.  We see this trait as early as age 
12, when He seemed puzzled that Mary and Joseph would look anywhere 
but the temple for Him.  All His life, He was a man on a mission. 
That's why so many were drawn to Him, and why a fisherman would drop 
his net in an instant to follow Him.

   The secular men's movement, for all its noise and drum-beating, 
lacks this sense of purpose. There is little vision, strength of 
conviction, or direction.  By contrast, Jesus not only knew where He 
was going, but He persevered in the face of trials and obstacles.  In 
Jerusalem, He would face not only the ridicule and cruelty of men, 
but the wrath and rejection of His own Father.  Yet the importance of 
the mission outweighed everything else.  His final cry, "It is 
finished!" was not a whimper, but a triumphant shout of victory.

   Men are made for a cause, for something outside themselves. The 
cause of Christ is eternal; it never dies.  To Paul, life wasn't just 
in Jesus, life was Jesus (Phil. 1:21). To be true men, we must orient 
ourselves to that same calling, that singular purpose.

      "The ultimate tender warrior" by Stu Weber. New Man, Jul/Aug 
1994 (Vol 1, No 1).  Pages 76-80. Topic: MASCULINITY. See also 9410 
and 9334.
!TOPICS
MASCULINITY
MEN'S MOVEMENT
ROLE MODELS
JESUS CHRIST
