!TITLE
THE LEADER AS PEOPLE-DEVELOPER
!WORDS
  » "One of the keys to effective leadership is the ability to 
develop and build up the people around you."«

   Successful leaders are people-builders.  They seek to develop the 
people around them in the following ways:
   Right assumptions.  Effective leaders understand that the way you 
view people will determine to a great extent how you treat them. You 
find what you look for, and what you find influences how you respond 
to another individual.
   Right attitudes.  It is essential to make people feel important.  
Follow the example of Napoleon.  He knew the name of every one of his 
officers and whenever he had the chance he would ask one of them 
about his hometown and family. Amazingly enough, he remembered a 
great deal of this information, thereby proving his genuine interest 
in his men.  No wonder they were extremely devoted to him.
   Right questions.  "People do not care how much you know until 
they know how much you care."
   Right vision.  People have a tendency to develop into what the 
important individuals in their lives think they can become. Have a 
vision for what your people can become and share that with them.  
Encouraging them will bring out the best.
   Right assistance.  Helping people in the right way produces 
tremendous loyalty.  Success is not learning how to avoid failure, 
but using failure as an opportunity to try again more intelligently.
 @Z:E

      "Do you have the skills to be a people- developer?" by John 
Maxwell.  Single Adult Ministries Journal, Issue 104, 1994. Pages 
15-16. Topic: LEADERSHIP QUALITIES.  See also 9477 and 9361.
!TOPICS
LEADERSHIP QUALITIES
