!TITLE
QUICK-QUOTE: 10155 THE CLOCK VS. THE COMPASS
!WORDS
  "Our struggle to put first things first can be characterized by the 
contrast of two powerful tools that direct us: the clock and the 
compass. The clock represents our commitments, appointments, 
schedules, goals, activities...how we manage our time.  The compass 
represents our vision, values, principles, mission, conscience, 
direction--what we feel is important and how we lead our lives.  The 
struggle comes when we sense a gap between the clock and the 
compass--when what we do doesn't contribute to what is most important 
in our lives."

                                --Stephen Covey in First Things 
First  (quoted in Youthworker, Spr 1995)
