!TITLE
RATING PRESIDENTIAL MORALITY
!WORDS
    » "Recent U.S. Presidents as a group are believed to have 
possessed just average ethical standards."«

   With another Presidential election approaching, we can expect 
intense media scrutiny of candidates.  The George H. Gallup 
International Institute asked 1,007 adult Americans to evaluate 
presidential ethics.

   When asked how they rated the ethical standards of recent 
presidents, only 4% said "very high" and only 13% said "high."  
Forty-two percent rated them average, and almost the same percentage 
rated them low or very low.

   With similar pessimism, only 13% felt recent presidents have done 
a good job of raising the moral and ethical standards of the nation 
as a whole.  Most (51%) rated the presidents as fair in this area, 
and 35% said "poor."

   Is the nation's moral health even an issue for presidents?  The 
question was asked, "Regardless of the kind of job you think recent 
presidents have been doing, how much influence do you think they 
could have on raising the moral and ethical standards of the 
nation?"  The majority (54%) said presidents could have a great deal 
of influence. Another 32% answered "some."  Only 12% believe 
presidents have little chance of affecting the moral climate of the 
nation.

   People were asked to rate the importance of these qualities in a 
president: high ethics, personal honesty, good family life, and 
strong religious faith.  Personal honesty and high ethics led the 
pack at 36% and 34%, respectively. Religious faith was rated highest 
by only 13% of those polled, and a good family life received 8% of 
the votes.

   Religious values are important, however.  Half those questioned 
said they were extremely important, and 39% said somewhat important.

  "Public wants presidents to be moral and ethical leaders."  
Emerging Trends, May 1995 (Vol 17, No 5).  Pages 1-2.  Topic: 
GOVERNMENT AND ETHICS. See also 10444.
!TOPICS
GOVERNMENT AND ETHICS
POLITICIANS
LEADERSHIP QUALITIES
INTEGRITY
MORALS
VALUES
EMERGING TRENDS, 9505. PP1-2.
