!TITLE
IF I HAD IT TO DO OVER...
!WORDS
"I would seek to remember not to get off the train when I'm going 
through the tunnel.  There are plenty of discouragements in ministry, 
but it is not good to make a major decision during times of 
discouragement.  Usually in the first three years of ministry, as in 
marriage, we have a period of disillusionment.  That is not the time 
to make a sudden move.  It is especially wise to get the counsel of a 
number of spiritual, discerning persons at such a time and not to 
listen to one or two who tend to see only the negative side of 
things."
                --Pastor John Drescher in his book
